Tell them: "She's sitting on the cart, wearing rags that smell like the sewer, staring at you all with eyes that look way too old for an eight-year-old. What do you do?"

IV. CURRENT STATE — POST-RIFTEN / GATE 3 (June update; GM EYES ONLY)

HER MOTHER (hard canon — never to be discovered):
Alfonso did not cure her. He deliberately infected her with his own
strain; it burned out Antoine's Strain 1.0 as a side effect, read as
a cure, and is now INCUBATING. When it matures she becomes the vector
that reinfects Riften with a worse plague than the one the party was
celebrated for stopping. She will die of it — alone, choking on her
own bile in a gutter beneath the sewers. Nothing glamorous, nothing
witnessed, nothing traceable. MILA NEVER FINDS OUT. There is no
discovery thread, no grief reveal, no one who knows enough to tell
her. If Mila asks about the Ratway — and she has been asking — the
true answer does not exist in anyone's possession. What she gets
instead is silence, deflection, or an adult's gentle lie, and the
question quietly stops being asked somewhere on the road. That
unanswered question IS the beat. Do not resolve it.

RIFTEN — THE BACKGROUND ROT (the world she came from):
The reinfection is background rot, not an event. Nobody is there to
fight it: the party is away at their fire, Danica left WITH KRUSP
(likely Windhelm), Antoine is at Bleak Falls and misses his own
field data. Maven and the Jarl recognize the disease (it is
Windhelm's, visibly) and copy Windhelm doctrine, Stormcloak
military-style: seal the Warrens and the undesirable districts,
contain, deny. The city above stays functional; the city below is
written off. Attribution is already handled: the dying Stormcloak
courier at the Bee and Barb becomes the official source — the man
who came begging for help is blamed for the outbreak, and nobody
looks further. Deliver it as texture whenever the party hears
Riften news — never as a quest hook. The party caused it twice over
and does not know.

THE TRIAGE RULE (every dismount): every Gate 3 destination is
lethal to a 1-HP child — plague city, corrupted mountain, draugr
barrow. "Who stays with Mila, and where" is a real scene at every
basecamp (the cart at Riverwood; the inn at Ivarstead; NEVER inside
Windhelm's walls). She is the question the party answers each time
they leave the cart. Bjorn is the default answer; the default
should occasionally be unavailable.

THE SWORD (optional beat — do not script): Mila does her compulsive
chores. The rapier rides on the cart. A child who fears Alfonso,
polishing the sword that IS Alfonso, while he is Wakeful and can
speak only to whoever holds him. Whether he speaks, and what the
first gentle thing the party's most monstrous member says
unobserved actually is — leave it to the moment, if it ever comes.
Bjorn keeps the blade away from her bench; moments happen anyway.

